content: Kim Kardashian West has reportedly canceled yet another scheduled appearance. The reality star was scheduled to make an appearance at Las Vegas' Hakkasan Nightclub on Oct. 28, one week after her 36th birthday. Kim had a $1m deal with the club for four appearances in 2016 and because she has already made two, one in April and one in July, she has two left before the end of the year. But sources close to the family say, Kim has not fully recovered from being robbed while in Paris.
title: Kim Kardashian West Cancels Birthday Bash

content: Thailand's revered King Bhumibol Adulyadej, the world's longest-reigning monarch, died Thursday. The 88-year-old had spent most of the last decade in a hospital for a variety of ailments related to old age, including kidney and lung problems. He had not been seen in public since January. The U.S.-born royal was a keen jazz saxophonist and held a patent for rain-making technology.
title: Thailand's King Bhumibol Adulyade Dies At Age 88

content: Support for legalization of marijuana has risen to nearly 60 percent among U.S. adults, according to a study published on Wednesday, marking a near reversal of attitudes held only a decade ago. More relaxed views about marijuana have led around two dozen states to allow legal access of some type of the drug and more U.S. states are set to vote on marijuana related measures on Nov. 8.
title: More U.S. Adults Want Marijuana Legalization

content: Beardogs are a rare species that one extinct over 37 million years ago. Beardogs were quadrupedal carnivorous mammals, and share evolutionary lines with foxes, weasels, wolves, bears, and domesticated dogs. Beardogs came in a variety of sizes. They could over one thousand pounds or the size of a tiny chihuahua. Unlike other carnivores, beardogs used their teeth to crush their prey, rather than use their teeth to tear through their flesh.
title: Extinct Beardogs Get a More Prominent Place in the Carnivore Family Tree

content: Britain's biggest retailer Tesco pulls Unilever goods such as Marmite from its website in a pricing row sparked by the Brexit-induced plunge in the pound. As David Pollard reports, it's one of the most vivid signs to date of how leaving the EU could hurt consumers.
title: Tesco, Unilever in Brexit price clash

content: According to the head of Marvel Studios, Kevin Feige, Captain Marvel wears the belt in this universe. In an interview with IGN, Kevin talked a bit about the inclusion of the character in the Marvel Cinematic Universe. This new version of Carol Danvers will have much more power than the one many fans are used to, as well as a bigger part in the universe than she has had for some time. Brie Larson will be starring as Captain Marvel, and her solo film is slated for release on March 8, 2019.
title: Captain Marvel And The Marvel Cinematic Universe

content: Sony Pictures Television is going to the Russians. It is expanding into Russia with local versions of The Good Wife, Doc Martin and Mad Dogs, as the country continues to see remakes of popular foreign shows. SPT's Russian production company Lean-M struck a development deal with national network NTV to produce local adaptations of the CBS hit show, The Good Wife and British crime drama Mad Dogs. Both are set to go into production next year.
title: 'The Good Wife' Russian Style

content: Lab animals consist of fruit flies, zebrafish, mice, and monkeys. What most people don’t know is that each species is bred, so that each specimen is almost exactly identical so experiment results are more reliable. Gene editing is making it possible for scientists to change the genetics of the lab animals. These new techniques will make studying lab animals that much more effective.
title: Lab Animals And Gene Editing

content: Officials said a man armed with an assault rifle and wearing a ballistic vest was killed after shooting two Boston police officers. They were responding to a domestic incident Wednesday night. Boston Police Commissioner Bill Evans said both officers were in "extremely critical" condition early Thursday. One of them is suffering life-threatening injuries from the dramatic shootout. The officers, who were not identified, were said to be a 28-year and a 12-year veteran of the department.
title: Two Boston Cops Shot

content: Tomo Brejc / The Look Jon Hamm isn't afraid to admit he's flawed, but he also isn't afraid to admit that he's put in the work to help fix those flaws. The 45-year-old actor sat down with Net-a-Porter's The Journal and opened up about his private life, which he's tried to keep under wraps and succeeded for the most part—except for making headlines after going to rehab in 2015 for alcoholism. While many may shy away from talking about such an experience, Hamm is more than open to do so.
title: Jon Hamm Opens Up About His Private Life to Net-a-Porter's The Journal
